description:
The investment seeks to track the investment results of the MSCI All Qatar Capped Index.
 The fund will invest at least 90% of its assets in the component securities of the index and in investments that have economic characteristics that are substantially identical to the component securities of the index. The index, which is designed to measure the equity market in Qatar, is a free float-adjusted market capitalization-weighted index with a capping methodology applied to issuer weights. The fund is non-diversified.
